## Explore Extended Detection & Response (XDR) use cases ##

Detection of Threat
Microsoft Defender for Endpoints (MDE) detects attacks, raises alert to security opeprations, provides
details about the threat. User access is disabled from the device while infected. MDE communicates to Intune
the risk level on the endpoint has changed. Intune triggers and marks the account as noncompliant, Microsoft
Entra ID blocks user access to apps.

Remediation
MDE - either automated remediated, analyst approval automated remediation, analys manual investigation of threat.
MDE adds information on the attack to Microsoft's Threat Intelligence system.

Share Intelligence and Restore Access
Once remediated, MDE signals Intune to change device risk status. Microsoft Entra ID allow access.
The threat signals in Microsoft Threat Intelligence are used by Microsoft tools to detect and remediate threats elsewhere.

Access Restricted
While Intune signals non-compliance, access is restricted. New requests are blocks, current access that supports Continuous
Access Evalution (CAE) are blocked also. This only applies to corporate resources (you can use youtube)

Acess Restored
After Remediation, access is restored. 
